author: RiseOfRest
text:
Atlanta is writing its own playbook where history and renewal, founders and Fortune 500s, civic vision and grassroots grit all converge. The result: a city ready to compete (and win) on the world stage. 

Thanks to everyone who welcomed us back.

author: TrendSpider
text: And so it begins.  $OSCR

author: RiseOfRest
text: .@TechSqATL embodies the paradox: extraordinary density of talent, research, and capital, spread across industries that must be woven together. As @CabreraAngel noted, the next decade is about stitching that fabric tight enough to reach top-five hub status.

author: RiseOfRest
text: One of Atlanta’s advantages is its industry diversity. From hard tech at @hermeuscorp to AI-powered architecture at @cove__inc, bleeding-edge innovation across sectors is happening here. The challenge: matching that breadth with the capital, connectivity, and recognition needed

author: RiseOfRest
text: Atlanta’s corporations also play a role. At @SageUSAmerica's  Discovery Center, we heard how the global company is doubling down on its commitment to ATL and using its state-of-the-art, AI-powered North America HQ to convene & connect local founders and small businesses.

author: RiseOfRest
text: We saw how @ATLTechVillage, @riceatlanta, @wei_atlanta & The Lola have each cultivated a distinct founder community. We also heard how, together, they create a network that reinforces & routs members to the right resources as they work toward the shared goal of helping Atlanta

author: RiseOfRest
text: From the @AtlantaBeltline to @TechSqATL to @sodowntownatl, Atlanta is drafting the blueprint for placemaking that fuels entrepreneurship: honor history, work with existing communities, and create vibrant neighborhoods, and business, growth, and talent follow.

author: RiseOfRest
text: Our conversation at @ATLTechVillage Sylvan set the tone: the city wants to be a top-five U.S. tech hub. That means 1000s of new startups, more pre-seed & seed capital, & big wins to signal “you can build here.” With #WorldCup2026 ahead, the global stage is set and the opportunity

author: RiseOfRest
text: When we first pulled into #Atlanta in 2015, the energy was palpable. A decade on, the city’s startup community is bigger, more ambitious, and more intentional, anchored by both new initiatives and seeds planted years ago.
